    h2. Blast Radius

    *What is the blast radius of this change: Global/Regional/AD/FD/Single-box?*
    {color:#00875a}Regional{color}

    *Impact*

    *What are the worst-case scenarios if things go wrong during this change?*

    {color:#00875a}If the image push fails, it will not impact anything. For the mapping change, worst case would be that OKE clusters might take a long time to come up. It can happen because of reconciliation that’s triggered when Cloud provider OCI container running on the KMIs need to be replaced. This can be caused by image attestation failures which may occur if the image attestation service is unable to attest the new image or if there is a latency in image attestation because of high load on image attestation service. If something goes wrong with the cloud-provider-oci image software itself, then customers might be unable to perform CRUD operations on their Load balancers, Persistent Volumes. Native Pod networking controller will also not work correctly.{color}

    Note:{color:#00875a}Each OKE cluster is single tenanted and comprised of 3 VMs (aka KMIs). If one of the KMIs received an update to use a non-existent image then that single KMI would not function and would be taken out of the call path of the customer. We would at worst lose one HA in this scenario.{color}

    *Which services will be impacted by this change when things go wrong, and how?*
    {color:#00875a}Any services using OKE for provisioning PVCs/LB's will be impacted if things go wrong after the release. In the worst case scenario LB/PVC operations will be stuck in pending state and CCM container running on KMI's will start crashing. Initialising worker nodes which use native pod networking will also not work{color}

    *Prevention*

    *What are you doing to ensure the worst-case scenarios do not happen?*
    * Post Upgrade testing was done in Integ environments to ensure safety against worst case scenario. The test included
    ** Ensuring no failures in existing pods, deployments volumes after the release.
    ** Testing attach / detach / mount / unmount of volumes in use prior and after the release.
    ** Ensure no change in behaviour of existing features including Block Volumes & Load Balancers.
    ** Ensuring no KMI reconcile failures and no workflows in stuck state.
    * End to End testing done in pre-prod test environments for kubernetes versions impacted by this CM.
    * To avoid failures from Image not being present, has been executed to push all required images.

    *Detection*

    *How will you know if there are failures and how quickly?*
    * Check if any Canary failures -[Canary Grafana|https://grafana.oci.oraclecorp.com/d/420420/oke-canary-metrics-data-plane-canary?orgId=1&refresh=5s&var-realm=oc1&var-region=us-ashburn-1&var-fleet=okecanaryla.data-plane-oke-canary-cb-prod-v2]
    ** There should be no failures in cluster creates in canary.
    ** Dataplane Canary includes creation/deletion/attach/detach/mount/unmount of volumes via PVC, there should not be any failures in dataplane canary after the release. Canary runs are triggered at a frequency of 15-30 minutes depending on when was the last successful run.
    * When multiple clusters have kube-apiserver in not ready state. Here is the link to metric -[kube-apiserver not ready metric|https://devops.oci.oraclecorp.com/t/t-muto].

    All the steps for finding failures and mitigation are described in detail in the "Validation" tab.

    *What are you doing to detect any failures before impact to the full blast radius?*
    * Dataplane canary includes creation/deletion/attach/detach/mount/unmount of volumes via PVC, there should not be any failures in dataplane canary after the release.
    * This is in the execution detailed plan. While the change is in progress Canary Runs, MQL alarms and Grafana will be monitored. The details steps are mentioned in "Validation" tab.

